text:
Aur bhai CSE ke chappu boi and wing ke sabse bakchod launde! Apan dono ka sab jgah almost sath me attendance rhta tha. Chahe wo first year ke lectures ho, ncc (altough u were in other group but attendance and frooti ke liye kya hi bhasad mach ti thi), summer me swimming and countless other involvements. First year me shobhit ke sath milkar humne bhot bakchodi ki hai. I cannot even recall all the games we have played together. Yaad hai jab overwatch free hua tha exam ke time ek week ke liye and fir  sudhanshu ke sath milkar resident evil khele the hum sari lights off kar ke. Tera wo first year wala epic GPL to puri wing ko humesha yaad rhega. And thanks to u I met several other amazing people (Aryan, tanmay). I don't know if I have mentioned it before but kabhi kabhi tanmay, aryan ke sath tu discuss karta tha to mujhe disturb na ho isliye main white noise laga leta tha headphone meü§£ Apan ne pta nhi kitne hi courses, assignments, projects sath me kiye honge and tune meri har jgah gaand bachai hai. You were always there to support me during internship, placements and many other challenging times. Jab bhi koi code me error aata u were my go to person. CPI almost perfect hai, mobile, pc gaming sab me pro hai and bulla bhi itna kat ta tha, koi itna bakchod kaise ho skta hai. I will miss all those random bulla sessions outside our gates (tere sath gate ke pass khade khade hi sare discussions hote the 3rd and 4th year meüòÇüòÇ). I don't know why you never joined music club (though I remember u did give auditions for freshers night). You have an amazing voice. Goa trip was one hell of an experience. Aur trips par chalte hai covid ke bad. Main bhi try karta hu bangalore aane ka next year. Tab tak ke liye Valo and pubg to hai hi. 
DOGE to the moon üöÄüöÄüöÄ
author: Arpit Kumar Jhunjhunwala

text: According to all known laws of aviation, there is no way that a bee should be able to fly. Its wings are too small to get its fat little body off the ground. The bee, of course, flies anyway. Because bees don‚Äôt care what humans think is impossible.‚Äù SEQ. 75 - ‚ÄúINTRO TO BARRY‚Äù INT. BENSON HOUSE - DAY ANGLE ON: Sneakers on the ground. Camera PANS UP to reveal BARRY BENSON‚ÄôS BEDROOM ANGLE ON: Barry‚Äôs hand flipping through different sweaters in his closet. BARRY Yellow black, yellow black, yellow black, yellow black, yellow black, yellow black...oohh, black and yellow... ANGLE ON: Barry wearing the sweater he picked, looking in the mirror. BARRY (CONT‚ÄôD) Yeah, let‚Äôs shake it up a little. He picks the black and yellow one. He then goes to the sink, takes the top off a CONTAINER OF HONEY, and puts some honey into his hair. He squirts some in his mouth and gargles. Then he takes the lid off the bottle, and rolls some on like deodorant. CUT TO: INT. BENSON HOUSE KITCHEN - CONTINUOUS Barry‚Äôs mother, JANET BENSON, yells up at Barry. JANET BENSON Barry, breakfast is ready! CUT TO: "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 1. INT. BARRY‚ÄôS ROOM - CONTINUOUS BARRY Coming! SFX: Phone RINGING. Barry‚Äôs antennae vibrate as they RING like a phone. Barry‚Äôs hands are wet. He looks around for a towel. BARRY (CONT‚ÄôD) Hang on a second! He wipes his hands on his sweater, and pulls his antennae down to his ear and mouth. BARRY (CONT'D) Hello? His best friend, ADAM FLAYMAN, is on the other end. ADAM Barry? BARRY Adam? ADAM Can you believe this is happening? BARRY Can‚Äôt believe it. I‚Äôll pick you up. Barry sticks his stinger in a sharpener. SFX: BUZZING AS HIS STINGER IS SHARPENED. He tests the sharpness with his finger. SFX: Bing. BARRY (CONT‚ÄôD) Looking sharp. ANGLE ON: Barry hovering down the hall, sliding down the staircase bannister. Barry‚Äôs mother, JANET BENSON, is in the kitchen. JANET BENSON Barry, why don‚Äôt you use the stairs? Your father paid good money for those. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 2. BARRY Sorry, I‚Äôm excited. Barry‚Äôs father, MARTIN BENSON, ENTERS. He‚Äôs reading a NEWSPAPER with the HEADLINE, ‚ÄúQueen gives birth to thousandtuplets: Resting Comfortably.‚Äù MARTIN BENSON Here‚Äôs the graduate. We‚Äôre very proud of you, Son. And a perfect report card, all B‚Äôs. JANET BENSON (mushing Barry‚Äôs hair) Very proud. BARRY Ma! I‚Äôve got a thing going here. Barry re-adjusts his hair, starts to leave. JANET BENSON You‚Äôve got some lint on your fuzz. She picks it off. BARRY Ow, that‚Äôs me! MARTIN BENSON Wave to us. We‚Äôll be in row 118,000. Barry zips off. BARRY Bye! JANET BENSON Barry, I told you, stop flying in the house! CUT TO: SEQ. 750 - DRIVING TO GRADUATION EXT. BEE SUBURB - MORNING A GARAGE DOOR OPENS. Barry drives out in his CAR. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 3. ANGLE ON: Barry‚Äôs friend, ADAM FLAYMAN, standing by the curb. He‚Äôs reading a NEWSPAPER with the HEADLINE: ‚ÄúFrisbee Hits Hive: Internet Down. Bee-stander: ‚ÄúI heard a sound, and next thing I knew...wham-o!.‚Äù Barry drives up, stops in front of Adam. Adam jumps in. BARRY Hey, Adam. ADAM Hey, Barry. (pointing at Barry‚Äôs hair) Is that fuzz gel? BARRY A little. It‚Äôs a special day. Finally graduating. ADAM I never thought I‚Äôd make it. BARRY Yeah, three days of grade school, three days of high school. ADAM Those were so awkward. BARRY Three days of college. I‚Äôm glad I took off one day in the middle and just hitchhiked around the hive. ADAM You did come back different. They drive by a bee who‚Äôs jogging. ARTIE Hi Barry! BARRY (to a bee pedestrian) Hey Artie, growing a mustache? Looks good. Barry and Adam drive from the suburbs into the city. ADAM Hey, did you hear about Frankie? "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 4. BARRY Yeah. ADAM You going to his funeral? BARRY No, I‚Äôm not going to his funeral. Everybody knows you sting someone you die, you don‚Äôt waste it on a squirrel. He was such a hot head. ADAM Yeah, I guess he could‚Äôve just gotten out of the way. The DRIVE through a loop de loop. BARRY AND ADAM Whoa...Whooo...wheee!! ADAM I love this incorporating the amusement park right into our regular day. BARRY I guess that‚Äôs why they say we don‚Äôt need vacations. CUT TO: SEQ. 95 - GRADUATION EXT. GRADUATION CEREMONY - CONTINUOUS Barry and Adam come to a stop. They exit the car, and fly over the crowd to their seats. * BARRY * (re: graduation ceremony) * Boy, quite a bit of pomp...under * the circumstances. * They land in their seats. BARRY (CONT‚ÄôD) Well Adam, today we are men. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 5. ADAM We are. BARRY Bee-men. ADAM Amen! BARRY Hallelujah. Barry hits Adam‚Äôs forehead. Adam goes into the rapture. An announcement comes over the PA. ANNOUNCER (V.O) Students, faculty, distinguished bees...please welcome, Dean Buzzwell. ANGLE ON: DEAN BUZZWELL steps up to the podium. The podium has a sign that reads: ‚ÄúWelcome Graduating Class of:‚Äù, with train-station style flipping numbers after it. BUZZWELL Welcome New Hive City graduating class of... The numbers on the podium change to 9:15. BUZZWELL (CONT‚ÄôD) ...9:15. (he clears his throat) And that concludes our graduation ceremonies. And begins your career at Honex Industries. BARRY Are we going to pick our job today? ADAM I heard it‚Äôs just orientation. The rows of chairs change in transformer-like mechanical motion to Universal Studios type tour trams. Buzzwell walks off stage. BARRY (re: trams) Whoa, heads up! Here we go. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 6. SEQ. 125 - ‚ÄúFACTORY‚Äù FEMALE VOICE (V.O) Keep your hands and antennas inside the tram at all times. (in Spanish) Dejen las manos y antennas adentro del tram a todos tiempos. BARRY I wonder what it‚Äôs going to be like? ADAM A little scary. Barry shakes Adam. BARRY AND ADAM AAHHHH! The tram passes under SIGNS READING: ‚ÄúHonex: A Division of Honesco: A Part of the Hexagon Group.‚Äù TRUDY Welcome to Honex, a division of Honesco, and a part of the Hexagon group. BARRY This is it! The Honex doors OPEN, revealing the factory. BARRY (CONT‚ÄôD) Wow. TRUDY We know that you, as a bee, have worked your whole life to get to the point where you can work for your whole life. Honey begins when our valiant pollen jocks bring the nectar to the hive where our top secret formula is automatically color-corrected, scent adjusted and bubble contoured into this... Trudy GRABS a TEST TUBE OF HONEY from a technician. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 7. TRUDY (CONT‚ÄôD) ...soothing, sweet syrup with its distinctive golden glow, you all know as... EVERYONE ON THE TRAM (in unison) H-o-n-e-y. Trudy flips the flask into the crowd, and laughs as they all scramble for it. ANGLE ON: A GIRL BEE catching the honey. ADAM (sotto) That girl was hot. BARRY (sotto) She‚Äôs my cousin. ADAM She is? BARRY Yes, we‚Äôre all cousins. ADAM Right. You‚Äôre right. TRUDY At Honex, we also constantly strive to improve every aspect of bee existence. These bees are stress testing a new helmet technology. ANGLE ON: A STUNT BEE in a HELMET getting hit with a NEWSPAPER, then a SHOE, then a FLYSWATTER. He gets up, and gives a ‚Äúthumb‚Äôs up‚Äù. The graduate bees APPLAUD. ADAM (re: stunt bee) What do you think he makes? BARRY Not enough. TRUDY And here we have our latest advancement, the Krelman. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 8. BARRY Wow, what does that do? TRUDY Catches that little strand of honey that hangs after you pour it. Saves us millions. ANGLE ON: The Krelman machine. Bees with hand-shaped hats on, rotating around a wheel to catch drips of honey. Adam‚Äôs hand shoots up. ADAM Can anyone work on the Krelman? TRUDY Of course. Most bee jobs are small ones. But bees know that every small job, if it‚Äôs done well, means a lot. There are over 3000 different bee occupations. But choose carefully, because you‚Äôll stay in the job that you pick for the rest of your life. The bees CHEER. ANGLE ON: Barry‚Äôs smile dropping slightly. BARRY The same job for the rest of your life? I didn‚Äôt know that. ADAM What‚Äôs the difference? TRUDY And you‚Äôll be happy to know that bees as a species haven‚Äôt had one day off in 27 million years. BARRY So you‚Äôll just work us to death? TRUDY (laughing) We‚Äôll sure try. Everyone LAUGHS except Barry. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 9. The tram drops down a log-flume type steep drop. Cameras flash, as all the bees throw up their hands. The frame freezes into a snapshot. Barry looks concerned. The tram continues through 2 doors. FORM DISSOLVE TO: SEQ. 175 - ‚ÄúWALKING THE HIVE‚Äù INT. HONEX LOBBY ANGLE ON: The log-flume photo, as Barry looks at it. ADAM Wow. That blew my mind. BARRY (annoyed) ‚ÄúWhat‚Äôs the difference?‚Äù Adam, how could you say that? One job forever? That‚Äôs an insane choice to have to make. ADAM Well, I‚Äôm relieved. Now we only have to make one decision in life. BARRY But Adam, how could they never have told us that? ADAM Barry, why would you question anything? We‚Äôre bees. We‚Äôre the most perfectly functioning society on Earth. They walk by a newspaper stand with A SANDWICH BOARD READING: ‚ÄúBee Goes Berserk: Stings Seven Then Self.‚Äù ANGLE ON: A BEE filling his car‚Äôs gas tank from a honey pump. He fills his car some, then takes a swig for himself. NEWSPAPER BEE (to the bee guzzling gas) Hey! Barry and Adam begin to cross the street. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 10. BARRY Yeah but Adam, did you ever think that maybe things work a little too well around here? They stop in the middle of the street. The traffic moves perfectly around them. ADAM Like what? Give me one example. BARRY (thinks) ...I don‚Äôt know. But you know what I‚Äôm talking about. They walk off. SEQ. 400 - ‚ÄúMEET THE JOCKS‚Äù SFX: The SOUND of Pollen Jocks. PAN DOWN from the Honex statue. J-GATE ANNOUNCER Please clear the gate. Royal Nectar Force on approach. Royal Nectar Force on approach. BARRY Wait a second. Check it out. Hey, hey, those are Pollen jocks. ADAM Wow. FOUR PATROL BEES FLY in through the hive‚Äôs giant Gothic entrance. The Patrol Bees are wearing fighter pilot helmets with black visors. ADAM (CONT‚ÄôD) I‚Äôve never seen them this close. BARRY They know what it‚Äôs like to go outside the hive. ADAM Yeah, but some of them don‚Äôt come back. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 11. The nectar from the pollen jocks is removed from their backpacks, and loaded into trucks on their way to Honex. A SMALL CROWD forms around the Patrol Bees. Each one has a PIT CREW that takes their nectar. Lou Loduca hurries a pit crew along: LOU LODUCA You guys did great! You‚Äôre monsters. You‚Äôre sky freaks! I love it! I love it! SCHOOL GIRLS are jumping up and down and squealing nearby. BARRY I wonder where those guys have just been? ADAM I don‚Äôt know. BARRY Their day‚Äôs not planned. Outside the hive, flying who-knows-where, doing who-knows-what. ADAM You can‚Äôt just decide one day to be a Pollen Jock. You have to be bred for that. BARRY Right. Pollen Jocks cross in close proximity to Barry and Adam. Some pollen falls off, onto Barry and Adam. BARRY (CONT‚ÄôD) Look at that. That‚Äôs more pollen than you and I will ever see in a lifetime. ADAM (playing with the pollen) It‚Äôs just a status symbol. I think bees make too big a deal out of it. BARRY Perhaps, unless you‚Äôre wearing it, and the ladies see you wearing it. ANGLE ON: Two girl bees. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 12. ADAM Those ladies? Aren‚Äôt they our cousins too? BARRY Distant, distant. ANGLE ON: TWO POLLEN JOCKS. JACKSON Look at these two. SPLITZ Couple of Hive Harrys. JACKSON Let‚Äôs have some fun with them. The pollen jocks approach. Barry and Adam continue to talk to the girls. GIRL 1 It must be so dangerous being a pollen jock. BARRY Oh yeah, one time a bear had me pinned up against a mushroom. He had one paw on my throat, and with the other he was slapping me back and forth across the face. GIRL 1 Oh my. BARRY I never thought I‚Äôd knock him out. GIRL 2 (to Adam) And what were you doing during all of this? ADAM Obviously I was trying to alert the authorities. The girl swipes some pollen off of Adam with a finger. BARRY (re: pollen) I can autograph that if you want. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 13. JACKSON Little gusty out there today, wasn‚Äôt it, comrades? BARRY Yeah. Gusty. BUZZ You know, we‚Äôre going to hit a sunflower patch about six miles from here tomorrow. BARRY Six miles, huh? ADAM (whispering) Barry. BUZZ It‚Äôs a puddle-jump for us. But maybe you‚Äôre not up for it. BARRY Maybe I am. ADAM (whispering louder) You are not! BUZZ We‚Äôre going, oh-nine hundred at JGate. ADAM (re: j-gate) Whoa. BUZZ (leaning in, on top of Barry) What do you think, Buzzy Boy? Are you bee enough? BARRY I might be. It all depends on what oh-nine hundred means. CUT TO: SEQ. 450 - ‚ÄúTHE BALCONY‚Äù "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 14. INT. BENSON HOUSE BALCONY - LATER Barry is standing on the balcony alone, looking out over the city. Martin Benson ENTERS, sneaks up behind Barry and gooses him in his ribs. MARTIN BENSON Honex! BARRY Oh, Dad. You surprised me. MARTIN BENSON (laughing) Have you decided what you‚Äôre interested in, Son? BARRY Well, there‚Äôs a lot of choices. MARTIN BENSON But you only get one. Martin LAUGHS. BARRY Dad, do you ever get bored doing the same job every day? MARTIN BENSON Son, let me tell you something about stirring. (making the stirring motion) You grab that stick and you just move it around, and you stir it around. You get yourself into a rhythm, it‚Äôs a beautiful thing. BARRY You know dad, the more I think about it, maybe the honey field just isn‚Äôt right for me. MARTIN BENSON And you were thinking of what, making balloon animals? That‚Äôs a bad job for a guy with a stinger. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 15. BARRY Well no... MARTIN BENSON Janet, your son‚Äôs not sure he wants to go into honey. JANET BENSON Oh Barry, you are so funny sometimes. BARRY I‚Äôm not trying to be funny. MARTIN BENSON You‚Äôre not funny, you‚Äôre going into honey. Our son, the stirrer. JANET BENSON You‚Äôre going to be a stirrer?! BARRY No one‚Äôs listening to me. MARTIN BENSON Wait until you see the sticks I have for you. BARRY I can say anything I want right now. I‚Äôm going to get an ant tattoo. JANET BENSON Let‚Äôs open some fresh honey and celebrate. BARRY Maybe I‚Äôll pierce my thorax! MARTIN BENSON (toasting) To honey! BARRY Shave my antennae! JANET BENSON To honey! "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 16. BARRY Shack up with a grasshopper, get a gold tooth, and start calling everybody ‚ÄúDawg.‚Äù CUT TO: SEQ. 760 - ‚ÄúJOB PLACEMENT‚Äù EXT. HONEX LOBBY - CONTINUOUS ANGLE ON: A BEE BUS STOP. One group of bees stands on the pavement, as another group hovers above them. A doubledecker bus pulls up. The hovering bees get on the top level, and the standing bees get on the bottom. Barry and Adam pull up outside of Honex. ADAM I can‚Äôt believe we‚Äôre starting work today. BARRY Today‚Äôs the day. Adam jumps out of the car. ADAM (O.C) Come on. All the good jobs will be gone. BARRY Yeah, right... ANGLE ON: A BOARD READING: ‚ÄúJOB PLACEMENT BOARD‚Äù. Buzzwell, the Bee Processor, is at the counter. Another BEE APPLICANT, SANDY SHRIMPKIN is EXITING. SANDY SHRIMPKIN Is it still available? BUZZWELL Hang on. (he looks at changing numbers on the board) Two left. And...one of them‚Äôs yours. Congratulations Son, step to the side please. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 17. SANDY SHRIMPKIN Yeah! ADAM (to Sandy, leaving) What did you get? SANDY SHRIMPKIN Picking the crud out. That is stellar! ADAM Wow. BUZZWELL (to Adam and Barry) Couple of newbies? ADAM Yes Sir. Our first day. We are ready. BUZZWELL Well, step up and make your choice. ANGLE ON: A CHART listing the different sectors of Honex. Heating, Cooling, Viscosity, Krelman, Pollen Counting, Stunt Bee, Pouring, Stirrer, Humming, Regurgitating, Front Desk, Hair Removal, Inspector No. 7, Chef, Lint Coordinator, Stripe Supervisor, Antennae-ball polisher, Mite Wrangler, Swatting Counselor, Wax Monkey, Wing Brusher, Hive Keeper, Restroom Attendant. ADAM (to Barry) You want to go first? BARRY No, you go. ADAM Oh my. What‚Äôs available? BUZZWELL Restroom attendant is always open, and not for the reason you think. ADAM Any chance of getting on to the Krelman, Sir? BUZZWELL Sure, you‚Äôre on. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 18. He plops the KRELMAN HAT onto Adam‚Äôs head. ANGLE ON: The job board. THE COLUMNS READ: ‚ÄúOCCUPATION‚Äù ‚ÄúPOSITIONS AVAILABLE‚Äù, and ‚ÄúSTATUS‚Äù. The middle column has numbers, and the right column has job openings flipping between ‚Äúopen‚Äù, ‚Äúpending‚Äù, and ‚Äúclosed‚Äù. BUZZWELL (CONT‚ÄôD) Oh, I‚Äôm sorry. The Krelman just closed out. ADAM Oh! He takes the hat off Adam. BUZZWELL Wax Monkey‚Äôs always open. The Krelman goes from ‚ÄúClosed‚Äù to ‚ÄúOpen‚Äù. BUZZWELL (CONT‚ÄôD) And the Krelman just opened up again. ADAM What happened? BUZZWELL Well, whenever a bee dies, that‚Äôs an opening. (pointing at the board) See that? He‚Äôs dead, dead, another dead one, deady, deadified, two more dead. Dead from the neck up, dead from the neck down. But, that‚Äôs life. ANGLE ON: Barry‚Äôs disturbed expression. ADAM (feeling pressure to decide) Oh, this is so hard. Heating, cooling, stunt bee, pourer, stirrer, humming, inspector no. 7, lint coordinator, stripe supervisor, antenna-ball polisher, mite wrangler-- Barry, Barry, what do you think I should-- Barry? Barry? "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 19. Barry is gone. CUT TO: SEQ. 775 - ‚ÄúLOU LODUCA SPEECH‚Äù EXT. J-GATE - SAME TIME Splitz, Jackson, Buzz, Lou and two other BEES are going through final pre-flight checks. Barry ENTERS. LOU LODUCA Alright, we‚Äôve got the sunflower patch in quadrant nine. Geranium window box on Sutton Place... Barry‚Äôs antennae rings, like a phone. ADAM (V.O) What happened to you? Where are you? Barry whispers throughout. BARRY I‚Äôm going out. ADAM (V.O) Out? Out where? BARRY Out there. ADAM (V.O) (putting it together) Oh no. BARRY I have to, before I go to work for the rest of my life. ADAM (V.O) You‚Äôre going to die! You‚Äôre crazy! Hello? BARRY Oh, another call coming in. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 20. ADAM (V.O) You‚Äôre cra-- Barry HANGS UP. ANGLE ON: Lou Loduca. LOU LODUCA If anyone‚Äôs feeling brave, there‚Äôs a Korean Deli on 83rd that gets their roses today. BARRY (timidly) Hey guys. BUZZ Well, look at that. SPLITZ Isn‚Äôt that the kid we saw yesterday? LOU LODUCA (to Barry) Hold it son, flight deck‚Äôs restricted. JACKSON It‚Äôs okay Lou, we‚Äôre going to take him up. Splitz and Jackson CHUCKLE. LOU LODUCA Really? Feeling lucky, are ya? A YOUNGER SMALLER BEE THAN BARRY, CHET, runs up with a release waiver for Barry to sign. CHET Sign here. Here. Just initial that. Thank you. LOU LODUCA Okay, you got a rain advisory today and as you all know, bees cannot fly in rain. So be careful. As always, (reading off clipboard) watch your brooms, hockey sticks, dogs, birds, bears, and bats. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 21. Also, I got a couple reports of root beer being poured on us. Murphy‚Äôs in a home because of it, just babbling like a cicada. BARRY That‚Äôs awful. LOU LODUCA And a reminder for all you rookies, bee law number one, absolutely no talking to humans. Alright, launch positions! The Jocks get into formation, chanting as they move. LOU LODUCA (CONT‚ÄôD) Black and Yellow! JOCKS Hello! SPLITZ (to Barry) Are you ready for this, hot shot? BARRY Yeah. Yeah, bring it on. Barry NODS, terrified. BUZZ Wind! - CHECK! JOCK #1 Antennae! - CHECK! JOCK #2 Nectar pack! - CHECK! JACKSON Wings! - CHECK! SPLITZ Stinger! - CHECK! BARRY Scared out of my shorts - CHECK. LOU LODUCA Okay ladies, let‚Äôs move it out. Everyone FLIPS their goggles down. Pit crew bees CRANK their wings, and remove the starting blocks. We hear loud HUMMING. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 22. LOU LODUCA (CONT'D) LOU LODUCA (CONT‚ÄôD) Pound those petunia's, you striped stem-suckers! All of you, drain those flowers! A FLIGHT DECK GUY in deep crouch hand-signals them out the archway as the backwash from the bee wings FLUTTERS his jump suit. Barry follows everyone. SEQ. 800 - ‚ÄúFLYING WITH THE JOCKS‚Äù The bees climb above tree tops in formation. Barry is euphoric. BARRY Whoa! I‚Äôm out! I can‚Äôt believe I‚Äôm out! So blue. Ha ha ha! (a beat) I feel so fast...and free. (re: kites in the sky) Box kite! Wow! They fly by several bicyclists, and approach a patch of flowers. BARRY (CONT'D) Flowers! SPLITZ This is blue leader. We have roses visual. Bring it around thirty degrees and hold. BARRY (sotto) Roses. JACKSON Thirty degrees, roger, bringing it around. Many pollen jocks break off from the main group. They use their equipment to collect nectar from flowers. Barry flies down to watch the jocks collect the nectar. JOCK Stand to the side kid, it‚Äôs got a bit of a kick. The jock fires the gun, and recoils. Barry watches the gun fill up with nectar. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 23. BARRY Oh, that is one Nectar Collector. JOCK You ever see pollination up close? BARRY No, Sir. He takes off, and the excess pollen dust falls causing the flowers to come back to life. JOCK (as he pollinates) I pick some pollen up over here, sprinkle it over here, maybe a dash over there, pinch on that one...see that? It‚Äôs a little bit of magic, ain‚Äôt it? The FLOWERS PERK UP as he pollinates. BARRY Wow. That‚Äôs amazing. Why do we do that? JOCK ...that‚Äôs pollen power, Kid. More pollen, more flowers, more nectar, more honey for us. BARRY Cool. The Jock WINKS at Barry. Barry rejoins the other jocks in the sky. They swoop in over a pond, kissing the surface. We see their image reflected in the water; they‚Äôre really moving. They fly over a fountain. BUZZ I‚Äôm picking up a lot of bright yellow, could be daisies. Don‚Äôt we need those? SPLITZ Copy that visual. We see what appear to be yellow flowers on a green field. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 24. They go into a deep bank and dive. BUZZ Hold on, one of these flowers seems to be on the move. SPLITZ Say again...Are you reporting a moving flower? BUZZ Affirmative. SEQ. 900 - ‚ÄúTENNIS GAME‚Äù The pollen jocks land. It is a tennis court with dozens of tennis balls. A COUPLE, VANESSA and KEN, plays tennis. The bees land right in the midst of a group of balls. KEN (O.C) That was on the line! The other bees start walking around amongst the immense, yellow globes. SPLITZ This is the coolest. What is it? They stop at a BALL on a white line and look up at it. JACKSON I don‚Äôt know, but I‚Äôm loving this color. SPLITZ (smelling tennis ball) Smells good. Not like a flower. But I like it. JACKSON Yeah, fuzzy. BUZZ Chemical-y. JACKSON Careful, guys, it‚Äôs a little grabby. Barry LANDS on a ball and COLLAPSES. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 25. BARRY Oh my sweet lord of bees. JACKSON Hey, candy brain, get off there! Barry attempts to pulls his legs off, but they stick. BARRY Problem! A tennis shoe and a hand ENTER FRAME. The hand picks up the ball with Barry underneath it. BARRY (CONT'D) Guys! BUZZ This could be bad. JACKSON Affirmative. Vanessa walks back to the service line, BOUNCES the ball. Each time it BOUNCES, the other bees cringe and GASP. ANGLE ON: Barry, terrified. Pure dumb luck, he‚Äôs not getting squished. BARRY (with each bounce) Very close...Gonna Hurt...Mamma‚Äôs little boy. SPLITZ You are way out of position, rookie. ANGLE ON: Vanessa serving. We see Barry and the ball up against the racket as she brings it back. She tosses the ball into the air; Barry‚Äôs eyes widen. The ball is STRUCK, and the rally is on. KEN Coming in at you like a missile! Ken HITS the ball back. Barry feels the g-forces. ANGLE ON: The Pollen Jocks watching Barry pass by them in SLOW MOTION. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 26. BARRY (in slow motion) Help me! JACKSON You know, I don't think these are flowers. SPLITZ Should we tell him? JACKSON I think he knows. BARRY (O.S) What is this?! Vanessa HITS a high arcing lob. Ken waits, poised for the return. We see Barry having trouble maneuvering the ball from fatigue. KEN (overly confident) Match point! He leans in to look at her badge. She SNAPS IT SHUT, VANESSA (CONT‚ÄôD) Oh, it‚Äôs real. HEAVILY ARMED GUARD Sorry ma‚Äôam. That‚Äôs a nice brooch, by the way. VANESSA Thank you. It was a gift. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 107. They ENTER the staging area. BARRY (V.O) Then, once we‚Äôre inside, we just pick the right float. VANESSA How about the Princess and the Pea? BARRY Yeah. VANESSA I can be the princess, and-- BARRY ...yes, I think-- VANESSA You could be-- BARRY I‚Äôve-- VANESSA The pea. BARRY Got it. CUT TO: EXT. FLOAT STAGING AREA - A FEW MOMENTS LATER Barry, dressed as a PEA, flies up and hovers in front of the princess on the ‚ÄúPrincess and the Pea‚Äù float. The float is sponsored by Inflat-a-bed and a SIGN READS: ‚ÄúInflat-a-bed: If it blows, it‚Äôs ours.‚Äù BARRY Sorry I‚Äôm late. Where should I sit? PRINCESS What are you? BARRY I believe I‚Äôm the pea. PRINCESS The pea? It‚Äôs supposed to be under the mattresses. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 108. BARRY Not in this fairy tale, sweetheart. PRINCESS I‚Äôm going to go talk to the marshall. BARRY You do that. This whole parade is a fiasco! She EXITS. Vanessa removes the step-ladder. The princess FALLS. Barry and Vanessa take off in the float. BARRY (CONT‚ÄôD) Let‚Äôs see what this baby will do. ANGLE ON: Guy with headset talking to drivers. HEADSET GUY Hey! The float ZOOMS by. A young CHILD in the stands, TIMMY, cries. CUT TO: EXT. FLOAT STAGING AREA - A FEW MOMENTS LATER ANGLE ON: Vanessa putting the princess hat on. BARRY (V.O) Then all we do is blend in with traffic, without arousing suspicion. CUT TO: EXT. THE PARADE ROUTE - CONTINUOUS The floats go flying by the crowds. Barry and Vanessa‚Äôs float CRASHES through the fence. CUT TO: "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 109. EXT. LA FREEWAY Vanessa and Barry speed, dodging and weaving, down the freeway. BARRY (V.O) And once we‚Äôre at the airport, there‚Äôs no stopping us. CUT TO: EXT. LAX AIRPORT Barry and Vanessa pull up to the curb, in front of an TSA AGENT WITH CLIPBOARD. TSA AGENT Stop. Security. Did you and your insect pack your own float? VANESSA (O.C) Yes. TSA AGENT Has this float been in your possession the entire time? VANESSA (O.C) Since the parade...yes. ANGLE ON: Barry holding his shoes. TSA AGENT Would you remove your shoes and everything in your pockets? Can you remove your stinger, Sir? BARRY That‚Äôs part of me. TSA AGENT I know. Just having some fun. Enjoy your flight. CUT TO: EXT. RUNWAY Barry and Vanessa‚Äôs airplane TAKES OFF. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 110. BARRY (O.C) Then, if we‚Äôre lucky, we‚Äôll have just enough pollen to do the job. DISSOLVE TO: SEQ. 4025 - ‚ÄúCOCKPIT FIGHT‚Äù INT. AIRPLANE Vanessa is on the aisle. Barry is on a laptop calculating flowers, pollen, number of bees, airspeed, etc. He does a ‚ÄúStomp‚Äù dance on the keyboard. BARRY Can you believe how lucky we are? We have just enough pollen to do the job. I think this is going to work, Vanessa. VANESSA It‚Äôs got to work. PILOT (V.O) Attention passengers. This is Captain Scott. I‚Äôm afraid we have a bit of bad weather in the New York area. And looks like we‚Äôre going to be experiencing a couple of hours delay. VANESSA Barry, these are cut flowers with no water. They‚Äôll never make it. BARRY I‚Äôve got to get up there and talk to these guys. VANESSA Be careful. Barry flies up to the cockpit door. CUT TO: INT. COCKPIT - CONTINUOUS A female flight attendant, ANGELA, is in the cockpit with the pilots. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 111. There‚Äôs a KNOCK at the door. BARRY (C.O) Hey, can I get some help with this Sky Mall Magazine? I‚Äôd like to order the talking inflatable travel pool filter. ANGELA (to the pilots, irritated) Excuse me. CUT TO: EXT. CABIN - CONTINUOUS Angela opens the cockpit door and looks around. She doesn‚Äôt see anybody. ANGLE ON: Barry hidden on the yellow and black ‚Äúcaution‚Äù stripe. As Angela looks around, Barry zips into the cockpit. CUT TO: INT. COCKPIT BARRY Excuse me, Captain. I am in a real situation here... PILOT (pulling an earphone back, to the co-pilot) What did you say, Hal? CO-PILOT I didn‚Äôt say anything. PILOT (he sees Barry) Ahhh! Bee! BARRY No, no! Don‚Äôt freak out! There‚Äôs a chance my entire species-- CO-PILOT (taking off his earphones) Ahhh! "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 112. The pilot grabs a ‚ÄúDUSTBUSTER‚Äù vacuum cleaner. He aims it around trying to vacuum up Barry. The co-pilot faces camera, as the pilot tries to suck Barry up. Barry is on the other side of the co-pilot. As they dosey-do, the toupee of the co-pilot begins to come up, still attached to the front. CO-PILOT (CONT'D) What are you doing? Stop! The toupee comes off the co-pilot‚Äôs head, and sticks in the Dustbuster. Barry runs across the bald head. BARRY Wait a minute! I‚Äôm an attorney! CO-PILOT Who‚Äôs an attorney? PILOT Don‚Äôt move. The pilot uses the Dustbuster to try and mash Barry, who is hovering in front of the co-pilot‚Äôs nose, and knocks out the co-pilot who falls out of his chair, hitting the life raft release button. The life raft inflates, hitting the pilot, knocking him into a wall and out cold. Barry surveys the situation. BARRY Oh, Barry. CUT TO: INT. AIRPLANE CABIN Vanessa studies her laptop, looking serious. SFX: PA CRACKLE. BARRY (V.O) (in captain voice) Good afternoon passengers, this is your captain speaking. Would a Miss Vanessa Bloome in 24F please report to the cockpit. And please hurry! "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 113. ANGLE ON: The aisle, and Vanessa head popping up. CUT TO: INT. COCKPIT Vanessa ENTERS. VANESSA What happened here? BARRY I tried to talk to them, but then there was a Dustbuster, a toupee, a life raft exploded...Now one‚Äôs bald, one‚Äôs in a boat, and they‚Äôre both unconscious. VANESSA Is that another bee joke? BARRY No. No one‚Äôs flying the plane. The AIR TRAFFIC CONTROLLER, BUD, speaks over the radio. BUD This is JFK control tower. Flight 356, what‚Äôs your status? Vanessa presses a button, and the intercom comes on. VANESSA This is Vanessa Bloome. I‚Äôm a florist from New York. BUD Where‚Äôs the pilot? VANESSA He‚Äôs unconscious and so is the copilot. BUD Not good. Is there anyone onboard who has flight experience? A BEAT. BARRY As a matter of fact, there is. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 114. BUD Who‚Äôs that? VANESSA Barry Benson. BUD From the honey trial? Oh great. BARRY Vanessa, this is nothing more than a big metal bee. It‚Äôs got giant wings, huge engines. VANESSA I can‚Äôt fly a plane. BARRY Why not? Isn‚Äôt John Travolta a pilot? VANESSA Yes? BARRY How hard could it be? VANESSA Wait a minute. Barry, we‚Äôre headed into some lightning. CUT TO: Vanessa shrugs, and takes the controls. SEQ. 4150 - ‚ÄúBARRY FLIES PLANE‚Äù INT. BENSON HOUSE The family is all huddled around the TV at the Benson house. ANGLE ON: TV. Bob Bumble is broadcasting. BOB BUMBLE This is Bob Bumble. We have some late-breaking news from JFK airport, where a very suspenseful scene is developing. Barry Benson, fresh off his stunning legal victory... "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 115. Adam SPRAYS a can of HONEY-WHIP into his mouth. ADAM That‚Äôs Barry. BOB BUMBLE ...is now attempting to land a plane, loaded with people, flowers, and an incapacitated flight crew. EVERYONE Flowers?! CUT TO: INT. AIR TRAFFIC CONTROL TOWER BUD Well, we have an electrical storm in the area, and two individuals at the controls of a jumbo jet with absolutely no flight experience. JEANETTE CHUNG Just a minute, Mr. Ditchwater, there‚Äôs a honey bee on that plane. BUD Oh, I‚Äôm quite familiar with Mr. Benson‚Äôs work, and his no-account compadres. Haven‚Äôt they done enough damage already? JEANETTE CHUNG But isn‚Äôt he your only hope right now? BUD Come on, technically a bee shouldn‚Äôt be able to fly at all. CUT TO: INT. COCKPIT. Barry REACTS BUD The wings are too small, their bodies are too big-- "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 116. BARRY (over PA) Hey, hold on a second. Haven‚Äôt we heard this million times? The surface area of the wings, and the body mass doesn‚Äôt make sense? JEANETTE CHUNG Get this on the air. CAMERAMAN You got it! CUT TO: INT. BEE TV CONTROL ROOM An engineer throws a switch. BEE ENGINEER Stand by. We‚Äôre going live. The ‚ÄúON AIR‚Äù sign illuminates. CUT TO: INT. VARIOUS SHOTS OF NEW HIVE CITY The news report plays on TV. The pollen jocks are sitting around, playing paddle-ball, Wheel-o, and one of them is spinning his helmet on his finger. Buzzwell is in an office cubicle, playing computer solitaire. Barry‚Äôs family and Adam watch from their living room. Bees sitting on the street curb turn around to watch the TV. BARRY Mr. Ditchwater, the way we work may be a mystery to you, because making honey takes a lot of bees doing a lot of small jobs. But let me tell you something about a small job. If you do it really well, it makes a big difference. More than we realized. To us, to everyone. That‚Äôs why I want to get bees back to doing what we do best. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 117. Working together. That‚Äôs the bee way. We‚Äôre not made of Jello. We get behind a fellow. Black and yellow. CROWD OF BEES Hello! CUT TO: INT. COCKPIT Barry is giving orders to Vanessa. BARRY Left, right, down, hover. VANESSA Hover? BARRY Forget hover. VANESSA You know what? This isn‚Äôt so hard. Vanessa pretends to HONK THE HORN. VANESSA (CONT‚ÄôD) Beep, beep! Beep, beep! A BOLT OF LIGHTNING HITS the plane. The plane takes a sharp dip. VANESSA (CONT‚ÄôD) Barry, what happened? BARRY (noticing the control panel) Wait a minute. I think we were on autopilot that whole time. VANESSA That may have been helping me. BARRY And now we‚Äôre not! VANESSA (V.O.) (folding her arms) Well, then it turns out I cannot fly a plane. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 118. BARRY (CONT'D) Vanessa struggles with the yoke. CUT TO: EXT. AIRPLANE The airplane goes into a steep dive. CUT TO: SEQ. 4175 - ‚ÄúCRASH LANDING‚Äù INT. J-GATE An ALERT SIGN READING: ‚ÄúHive Alert. We Need:‚Äù Then the SIGNAL goes from ‚ÄúTwo Bees‚Äù ‚ÄúSome Bees‚Äù ‚ÄúEvery Bee There Is‚Äù Lou Loduca gathers the pollen jocks at J-Gate. LOU LODUCA All of you, let‚Äôs get behind this fellow. Move it out! The bees follow Lou Loduca, and EXIT J-Gate. CUT TO: INT. AIRPLANE COCKPIT BARRY Our only chance is if I do what I would do, and you copy me with the wings of the plane! VANESSA You don‚Äôt have to yell. BARRY I‚Äôm not yelling. We happen to be in a lot of trouble here. VANESSA It‚Äôs very hard to concentrate with that panicky tone in your voice. BARRY It‚Äôs not a tone. I‚Äôm panicking! CUT TO: "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 119. EXT. JFK AIRPORT ANGLE ON: The bees arriving and massing at the airport. CUT TO: INT. COCKPIT Barry and Vanessa alternately SLAP EACH OTHER IN THE FACE. VANESSA I don‚Äôt think I can do this. BARRY Vanessa, pull yourself together. Listen to me, you have got to snap out of it! VANESSA You snap out of it! BARRY You snap out of it! VANESSA You snap out of it! BARRY You snap out of it! VANESSA You snap out of it! CUT TO: EXT. AIRPLANE A GIGANTIC SWARM OF BEES flies in to hold the plane up. CUT TO: INT. COCKPIT - CONTINUOUS BARRY You snap out of it! VANESSA You snap out of it! "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 120. BARRY You snap-- VANESSA Hold it! BARRY (about to slap her again) Why? Come on, it‚Äôs my turn. VANESSA How is the plane flying? Barry‚Äôs antennae ring. BARRY I don‚Äôt know. (answering) Hello? CUT TO: EXT. AIRPLANE ANGLE ON: The underside of the plane. The pollen jocks have massed all around the underbelly of the plane, and are holding it up. LOU LODUCA Hey Benson, have you got any flowers for a happy occasion in there? CUT TO: INT. COCKPIT Lou, Buzz, Splitz, and Jackson come up alongside the cockpit. BARRY The pollen jocks! VANESSA They do get behind a fellow. BARRY Black and yellow. LOU LODUCA (over headset) Hello. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 121. Alright you two, what do you say we drop this tin can on the blacktop? VANESSA What blacktop? Where? I can‚Äôt see anything. Can you? BARRY No, nothing. It‚Äôs all cloudy. CUT TO: EXT. RUNWAY Adam SHOUTS. ADAM Come on, you‚Äôve got to think bee, Barry. Thinking bee, thinking bee. ANGLE ON: Overhead shot of runway. The bees are in the formation of a flower. In unison they move, causing the flower to FLASH YELLOW AND BLACK. BEES (chanting) Thinking bee, thinking bee. CUT TO: INT. COCKPIT We see through the swirling mist and clouds. A GIANT SHAPE OF A FLOWER is forming in the middle of the runway. BARRY Wait a minute. I think I‚Äôm feeling something. VANESSA What? BARRY I don‚Äôt know, but it‚Äôs strong. And it‚Äôs pulling me, like a 27 million year old instinct. Bring the nose of the plane down. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 122. LOU LODUCA (CONT'D) EXT. RUNWAY All the bees are on the runway chanting ‚ÄúThinking Bee‚Äù. CUT TO: INT. CONTROL TOWER RICK What in the world is on the tarmac? ANGLE ON: Dave OTS onto runway seeing a flower being formed by millions of bees. BUD Get some lights on that! CUT TO: EXT. RUNWAY ANGLE ON: AIRCRAFT LANDING LIGHT SCAFFOLD by the side of the runway, illuminating the bees in their flower formation. INT. COCKPIT BARRY Vanessa, aim for the flower! VANESSA Oh, okay? BARRY Cut the engines! VANESSA Cut the engines? BARRY We‚Äôre going in on bee power. Ready boys? LOU LODUCA Affirmative. CUT TO: "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 123. INT. AIRPLANE COCKPIT BARRY Good, good, easy now. Land on that flower! Ready boys? Give me full reverse. LOU LODUCA Spin it around! The plane attempts to land on top of an ‚ÄúAloha Airlines‚Äù plane with flowers painted on it. BARRY (V.O) I mean the giant black and yellow pulsating flower made of millions of bees! VANESSA Which flower? BARRY That flower! VANESSA I‚Äôm aiming at the flower! The plane goes after a FAT GUY IN A HAWAIIAN SHIRT. BARRY (V.O) That‚Äôs a fat guy in a flowered shirt! The other other flower! The big one. He snaps a photo and runs away. BARRY (CONT'D) Full forward. Ready boys? Nose down. Bring your tail up. Rotate around it. VANESSA Oh, this is insane, Barry. BARRY This is the only way I know how to fly. CUT TO: "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 124. AIR TRAFFIC CONTROL TOWER BUD Am I koo-koo kachoo, or is this plane flying in an insect-like pattern? CUT TO: EXT. RUNWAY BARRY (V.O) Get your nose in there. Don‚Äôt be afraid of it. Smell it. Full reverse! Easy, just drop it. Be a part of it. Aim for the center! Now drop it in. Drop it in, woman! The plane HOVERS and MANEUVERS, landing in the center of the giant flower, like a bee. The FLOWERS from the cargo hold spill out onto the runway. INT. AIPLANE CABIN The passengers are motionless for a beat. PASSENGER Come on already! They hear the ‚Äúding ding‚Äù, and all jump up to grab their luggage out of the overheads. SEQ. 4225 - ‚ÄúRUNWAY SPEECH‚Äù EXT. RUNWAY - CONTINUOUS The INFLATABLE SLIDES pop out the side of the plane. The passengers escape. Barry and Vanessa slide down out of the cockpit. Barry and Vanessa exhale a huge breath. VANESSA Barry, we did it. You taught me how to fly. Vanessa raises her hand up for a high five. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 125. BARRY Yes. No high five. VANESSA Right. ADAM Barry, it worked. Did you see the giant flower? BARRY What giant flower? Where? Of course I saw the flower! That was genius, man. Genius! ADAM Thank you. BARRY But we‚Äôre not done yet. Barry flies up to the wing of the plane, and addresses the bee crowd. BARRY (CONT‚ÄôD) Listen everyone. This runway is covered with the last pollen from the last flowers available anywhere on Earth. That means this is our last chance. We‚Äôre the only ones who make honey, pollinate flowers, and dress like this. If we‚Äôre going to survive as a species, this is our moment. So what do you all say? Are we going to be bees, or just Museum of Natural History key chains? BEES We‚Äôre bees! KEYCHAIN BEE Keychain! BARRY Then follow me... Except Keychain. BUZZ Hold on Barry. You‚Äôve earned this. Buzz puts a pollen jock jacket and helmet with Barry‚Äôs name on it on Barry. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 126. BARRY I‚Äôm a pollen jock! (looking at the jacket. The sleeves are a little long) And it‚Äôs a perfect fit. All I‚Äôve got to do are the sleeves. The Pollen Jocks toss Barry a gun. BARRY (CONT‚ÄôD) Oh yeah! ANGLE ON: Martin and Janet Benson. JANET BENSON That‚Äôs our Barry. All the bees descend upon the flowers on the tarmac, and start collecting pollen. CUT TO: SEQ. 4250 - ‚ÄúRE-POLLINATION‚Äù EXT. SKIES - CONTINUOUS The squadron FLIES over the city, REPOLLINATING trees and flowers as they go. Barry breaks off from the group, towards Vanessa‚Äôs flower shop. CUT TO: EXT. VANESSA‚ÄôS FLOWER SHOP - CONTINUOUS Barry REPOLLINATES Vanessa‚Äôs flowers. CUT TO: EXT. CENTRAL PARK - CONTINUOUS ANGLE ON: Timmy with a frisbee, as the bees fly by. TIMMY Mom, the bees are back! "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 127. Central Park is completely repollinated by the bees. DISSOLVE TO: INT. HONEX - CONTINUOUS Honex is back to normal and everyone is busily working. ANGLE ON: Adam, putting his Krelman hat on. ADAM If anyone needs to make a call, now‚Äôs the time. I‚Äôve got a feeling we‚Äôll be working late tonight! The bees CHEER. CUT TO: SEQ. 4355 EXT: VANESSA‚ÄôS FLOWER SHOP With a new sign out front. ‚ÄúVanessa & Barry: Flowers, Honey, Legal Advice‚Äù DISSOLVE TO: INT: FLOWER COUNTER Vanessa doing a brisk trade with many customers. CUT TO: INT: FLOWER SHOP - CONTINUOUS Vanessa is selling flowers. In the background, there are SHELVES STOCKED WITH HONEY. VANESSA (O.C.) Don‚Äôt forget these. Have a great afternoon. Yes, can I help who‚Äôs next? Who‚Äôs next? Would you like some honey with that? It is beeapproved. SIGN ON THE BACK ROOM DOOR READS: ‚ÄúBarry Benson: Insects at Law‚Äù. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 128. Camera moves into the back room. ANGLE ON: Barry. ANGLE ON: Barry‚Äôs COW CLIENT. COW Milk, cream, cheese...it‚Äôs all me. And I don‚Äôt see a nickel. BARRY Uh huh? Uh huh? COW (breaking down) Sometimes I just feel like a piece of meat. BARRY I had no idea. VANESSA Barry? I‚Äôm sorry, have you got a moment? BARRY Would you excuse me? My mosquito associate here will be able to help you. Mooseblood ENTERS. MOOSEBLOOD Sorry I‚Äôm late. COW He‚Äôs a lawyer too? MOOSEBLOOD Ma‚Äôam, I was already a bloodsucking parasite. All I needed was * a briefcase. * ANGLE ON: Flower Counter. VANESSA (to customer) Have a great afternoon! (to Barry) Barry, I just got this huge tulip order for a wedding, and I can‚Äôt get them anywhere. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 129. BARRY Not a problem, Vannie. Just leave it to me. Vanessa turns back to deal with a customer. VANESSA You‚Äôre a life-saver, Barry. (to the next customer) Can I help who‚Äôs next? Who‚Äôs next? ANGLE ON: Vanessa smiling back at Barry. Barry smiles too, then snaps himself out of it. BARRY (speaks into his antennae) Alright. Scramble jocks, it‚Äôs time to fly! VANESSA Thank you, Barry! EXT. FLOWER SHOP - CONTINUOUS ANGLE ON: Ken and Andy walking down the street. KEN (noticing the new sign) Augh! What in the world? It‚Äôs that bee again! ANDY (guiding Ken protectively) Let it go, Kenny. KEN That bee is living my life! When will this nightmare end? ANDY Let it all go. They don‚Äôt break stride. ANGLE ON: Camera in front of Barry as he flies out the door and up into the sky. Pollen jocks fold in formation behind him as they zoom into the park. BARRY (to Splitz) Beautiful day to fly. "Bee Movie" - JS REVISIONS 8/13/07 130. JACKSON Sure is. BARRY Between you and me, I was dying to get out of that office. FADE OUT: "Bee Movie"

text: CHD introduced us (probably in ESO207A class) (Good old days when I use to regular in classes :P). I still remember I came to your room an hour before EE200 endsem. You taught me so well that I pretty confident ki paper aache se nikal jayaga. I was very sad when I found you didn‚Äôt qualify for regionals in the sophomore year despite performing well compared to teams who just started competitive programming just before regional and qualified. You were one of the people I know who wants to work very hard and make his parents proud. They would be the happiest people one will ever see when you will graduate. Most of the people in our dept just converted to double major CSE just because they can increase the chances of a good internship. But you were one of those rare people who really wanted to do it. I‚Äôm pretty confident you will do very well in whatever you decide to do. Good Luck and All the Best man.  <3

text:
Are mera bhai hentai üôÉ..
Pretty sure maine tereko hentai bulana nhi shuru kiya tha do not blame me, although mai tereko bhot easily blame kar sakta hu for pari wala photo viral karna wing me aur behen wala harkat shuru karne ke liye. bhot kuch hai likhne ke liye yaar tere liye to starting from 1st year summers jab we actually came to know each other well uske phle to it was mostly formal talk types... tmhari baat karni ki speed aur style me training lena padta hai logo ko to understand what u are trying to say but iss chiz me mastery hai mereko hehe... first year summer project was one of the highlights wo roz roz ke nightouts and then tmhari first and the only gpl jisme ro diye the tm (sorry uske liye üòõüòõ ). Then u started watching animes  isme bhi mera influence tha iska credit le sakte hai hm üò¨üò¨üòé.. U are really easy to talk to the only person jiske room pe hm raat ko 3 baje bas aise hi aa jate the kuki kuch karne ko nhi hota tha and then we used to talk about so many animes till breakfast ya atleast dawn.. another highlight would be wo subah 4-5 baje ka cold weather me badminton not because hmlog jaldi uth gaye the but because hmlog uss waqt club se wapas aate the ya flying se wapas aate the... yaar ye sab khatam ho gaya still aisa lag rha ki aaj raat wapas nightout maarne jana hai...  You are probably one of the most caring persons i know and utne hi chutiye bhi ho for the very same reason... Iske alawa wo bombay and delhi wale trips has to be a major highlight in our  college lifes. Plus wo delhi wala to alag hi scene ho gaya tha but kaafi maza aaya tha udhar bhi apan teen log hi sirf gaye the (that was epic)... Teckriti ke phle one night before design change and plane wapas banane ka frustration bhi ek memory hi ban gaya hai ab to... Plus tm galaxy me bhi the saath me jisme kaam bhigadte zada the tm and then fraud marne lagte the tm aur sarthak aur anjesh .. Last ke days bhi apan bhot time saath rhe the and bhot baate kari thi tmhare saath pata hi nhi chalta tha kaise time paar ho gaya... College shuru hua tha to lagta tha kya bhai bhai bana rhe sabko but abhi ekdum brother from another mother wali feel aati hai terese.. tu jis din gaya tha wo din bhi bhot emotional day tha ü•∫...  Yaar tereko pareshaan karna bhot miss karenge but chill hai apne anime talks will go on and i seriously want to meet u soon i good health till then take care aur all the best... cheers ü•Ç.. miss you üñ§üñ§
PS - wo tmhari first drunken night koi nhi bhulega jitne log uss din wing me the 
PPS - Apni photos bhot kam hai saath mai zada le leni chahiyr thi ( the only regret üò∂)

text:
Jangid bhai!
Sach mai yaar, humne IITK mai 60% (maybe 70% ?) time share kiya hai, aur courses toh shayad almost saare hi share kare hai, mera humesha ka bulla partner üòõ First year me humne saath mai almost har exam ke liye last moment mai nightout maara thaa, aur yeh phir all the way through Civil ke courses tak continue raha! Tune apne badminton ke chaapu talent se Ritambhara mai volunteer banwaya thaa, aur phir kya swag mai Rahul tu aur mai queue tod ke sidhe final night mai entry liye thee, although badges bnane pade the but they were fun because of the presence there of you know who üòâ Inti sahi friendship huyi apni ki second year mai roomies hi ban gye. Woh tera har 15 days mai apni table ki position change karna, tera woh "Don't Let Me Down" wala ganda alarm, MOS ke liye library tak jana aur surprise quiz mai kabhi kuch nhi btana, ART mai teri "PUBG" wali drawing üòÇ Ajstyle bas PUBG mai badi badi baatein karna jaanta thaa, khelna nahi üòÇ Tera cement wali lab ka video viral karna reh gya yaar, kya sahi mix kar rha thaa tu üòÇ Girish ka puri D2 ki neend todna "Jangid" kehke, hydro ki saari classes tujhe apni cycle pe le jaana, tera last moment pe aake mere room mai uska project karna. Itni saari acchi memories hai, forever yaad rahengi bro, one of my best friends. Aur haan tera final sem ka MR waala kaand, woh toh prof ne jyada kuch kiya nhi, warna sidhe Tonk aake teri pitai karta üòú Chaapta reh aur apni dosti humesha aesi hi rhe, all the best bro!

Poker sessions kaafi enjoy kiye tere saath. Mission Impossible 6 jaane ke liye sab kat rhe the wing mai but tu saath rha üòÑ Goa trip pe kaafi maze aaye, aur tu driving bohot hi mast karta hai yaar, clubbed with your awesome playlists. Crypto gawd apni coolness se chapta rhe. All the best bro and jald hi chalte hai next trip pe!
author: Ashutosh  Sharma

text:
YO BABLOO BITCH, wing's fitness freak. (lol)

So I'm gonna try to express the gratitude and love I have for you because otherwise if I say in the wing group, you guys are gonna throw the tag of "meetha meetha".

It's been truly truly amazing 4 years in campus and you play a major role. Everyone who knows me outside of the wing also knows how much I praise my wingies, especially you. 
Do you remember that PHY103 endsem night!!! FUCK, uss din mujhe pata chala ki 100kilo ka aadmi ek chhoti si chair pe so sakta hai. I also learnt that summers ki Bhavesh can go without a bath for a month in May, DISGUSTING BC. Oh and you were so generous in second year ki you allowed a mouse to stay in the same room, divine soul you are. Lastly, thanks for introducing the wing to all types of bad things, without you it wasn't possible and I mean it. I have never seen a person with stronger will to manipulate me to have a drink xD.

I'm not saying ki hope to stay in touch, because we are going to. But I am going to say thanks for every factor of your personality because it made my campus life a little better always.
Much love bro, thoda meetha memoir chalta hai!
author: Atharv  Tyagi

text:
Yo Suppu!!
Mere bhai and same baap ki badnaseeb aulaad
Mere jitne sone aur nahane ka passion bas tu hi share krta h puri wing me üòÖ. Lekin atleast meri jacket white se Yellow to nhi hoti (you beat me there lol). Hum bhaiyo me tu hi h eklota artist. Chaapuüòù Violin aur drams dono kr leta h. Siraj ne tujhse bada violin bajwaya uske alawa to tune kabhi sunaya hi nhi hume to kuch. Waise hi bengali hone se reputation kharab thi upar se saale drams aur join kr liya üòÇ. Isse kahta h true courage to. 
Inn sab ke alawa programming god to tu h hi. Pura first year Shubham aur tune ki apna dabdaba banaye rakha üòÇ. Tujhse kitne bhi logical yaa kaise bhi discussion krwalo maza aata h yr. Rational aur itne sexy arguments deta h apna suppu. Defence mechanism word se hubahu tune hi kraya (abhi bhi tharwani ka weak point h ye üòÇ). Tere jitna chicken pelte hue kisi ko nhi dekha kasam se üòÇ. True non veg h tu (itna non veg ki baaki non veg bhi uncomfortable ho jaye). Baaki wing me chakkar lgate hue yaa phone pe baat krte hue paaya jaata tha tu mostly wing me. Ek sexy trip krle hamare saath bhi bhai, Maana ki hum drams ke yaa bengali nhi but dost to h bhai üòÇ. Teri drams performnace dekhne aaye h yr hamesha itna to payback banta h. 
Chal milte h kabhi phir. Jab tk annoy krta rha apne aaju baaju walo ko with a pinch of gyaan ofc, kuch bhi bolke smile krta rha jaise kya joke maara ho üòÇ, aur nobel milne pe bhul naa jaana bs yaa tab tk pagla naa jaana (physics wala bhadwe hote hi aise h).
Take care bro. Good luck. Milte h ‚ù§Ô∏è

text: Tere bina kaise hi khatam ho sakti mere campus ki khani....m kabhi soch bhi nahi sakta tha ki IITK mujhe bilkul mere hi jaise kisi insaan se mila degi,though you're much backchod than me obviously. Intern m randi rone se suru hui ye dosti kise pata tha zindgi bhar rhne wali hai. Iss dosti ki gahrai ka andaza keval iss baat se lgaya jaa sakta ki last k ek mahine m 50% gaali maine keval tujhe di. Kisi ki leni ho, raat ko ghoomne chalna ho, breakfast m, lunch m, dinner m,wing m football k time, ya stairs par baithkar duniyadaari discuss karte time, cricket khelne jaate time, shaam ki canteen waali chai k time, OAT m backchodi k time, har party m, late night lambi walk par, ya hall ki chhat par ho, ya OAT rooftop par pizza khate time, har moment m I can remeber you. kya sahi jamti hai yar apni...Ek poore group m ham 2 apna khud ka joke maarkar has lete hai...I started to know you by heart during lockdown and it's always a joy to be around you. Randiputram k inventor k baare m jitni taareefe likhi jaaye utni kam padengi. Bhai ka dil intern k time aisa toota ki placement m ek tarfa jalwe the. Ladkiyaan to khud aakar takrati hai bhai se :), but damn! who cares, bhai apna sakht launda hai aise thode hi pighal jaayega, lekin fir hall aakar ussi raaste par wapas jaane k liye tadpna, that incident I'm gonna tell everyone ahead and we're gonna laugh forever on that. Talent aur dimaag ki koi kami nahi hai, bas wo aajkal hentai k technical anal-ysis m kharch ho jaata hai, Just remebering your name is sufficent to put a big smile on my face, bhai kaas ham log first year m hi mil jaate to mere liye IIT ki duniya hi kuch aur hoti, khair jitna 1 mahine m zinda dili se ham ziye, wo 1.5 saal ki kami ko zaroor poora kar deti hai, Thank you for arranging stay in delhi for me and someeone :) when I was coming back from pune, thouhg meri kismat chutiya nikli. Kitne hi nakam plan hamne saath bnaye hai, IIT m har illegel cheez saath m try kari hai, kya hi aura hai iss dosti ka ki bas ek doosre ki taraf dekhkar hi duniyadaari bhoolkar hasi nikal jaati hai. Tera rista to m kara k hi chhorunga, as I have bragged about you infront of everyone I had known, but m kya karoo log self reject maar lete, itne badi hasi k baare m sunkar. Khair kosis zaari hai, manali ya chandigarh m try maarenge ya jahan bhi rahenge. I was always laughing whwneve I was there with you. Thanks bhai for everything. One thing I definitely miss is to be with you again and making fun of every possibility in this world. I wish I can stay forever in your aura. I'm so much excited to see you again and that's the first thing I'm gonna execute after this pandemic, see you soon brother...:)
author: Kuldeep  Singh

text: To chaliye milate hai tumhe apni chapu dost Jaya se jo whatsapp DP tak lgane m dimaag lgati hai....CC m ghanto bitane waali jaya ki bakchodi wali personality, kam hi log dekh paaye, I was one of those luckey persons. This rivelry started from second year and of course will contiue forever... but let me recall those last few years... we got to know each other after our first long talk in CC, again jahan ham dono apna apna rr kiye the, isme ham dono hmesha ek doosre se compete karte, kyuki kahin aur tumse compete karne ki meri aukaat nahi hai....I got a chance a to look at the human inside you after my favourite treat of momos given by you, kya hi thi wo raat, we almost became business partners on that day bas business abhi tak nahi khul paaya apna, I hope aage khul paayega. But that business idea was as unique as this friendship is: "ek dukhi insaan ko doosre jyada dukhi insaan se milwana". We both inspired each other ki fraud kaise maarna hota hai, whether it was a project under Himanshu sir, or was it a course under arnab. Khair padhai likhai se door chalte hai kyuki yahan tum ulta mujhe inspire karti ho, aur bakchodi par wapas aate hai, I remember that unique exam of all the tharki boys you took in chemical freshers "Jisme hme 20 30 ladkiyon k naam btane the from our batch" and we all failed in that. We both shared the same interests whether it was a trip plan to Goa (Jo wahan hoga, wo wahin rah jaayega) or it was a boring subject of mass transfer (of course I still have that sketch made by you in mass transfer class). Things always got spicy between us whenever we used to plan someone's marriage on OAT rooftop or discuss someone's breakup in NCL or in long night walks. I'm blessed to have a friend like you jo hmesha mere khane ka payment kar deta, you were the reason I got a chance to visit GH's canteen, wrna m kahan himmat kar pata GH m ghusne ki. Even though it's been a while since I met yoo last time but never felt that you're ever going away from me, this friendship is still as strong as it was ever(though tera phone abhi tak thik nahi hua).....Yar ek trip se kya hoga, mujhe jyada karne hai but pata nahi kab tum ghar se nikalogi, m to hmesha taiyar hoo tere saath bhagne ko but it seems mujhe hi aana padega tujhe tere ghar se kidnap karne....I wanted to roam around again in those lonely streets of campus but I missed that chance.... I miss you buddy... I hope this wait will be over soon and I will get a chance to discuss another dukh bhari khani of someone with you on a "treat by you". I'll always be there for any sort of bakchodi with you just never forget to ping me once....
author: Kuldeep  Singh

text: Bhai ab to btade campus m kon pasand hai...I can't remember a single moment jab ham ek doosre ko dekhkar na hase ho, bc itni bhi joker jaisi sakal nahi hai, par hasi to aa hi jaati, I was never in even a percent of you but always tried to catch up to you, Bhai tu hai chapu maan le, Bahut RR machata hai, fir hmi ko chhorkar aage badh jaata hai, ham ussi bakchodi m fase rah jaate, Lucknow shaandar tha but usse bhi shaandaar wo raat, How can I forget our "Aishwrya rai" dancing on "Kajra re" and then that stud guy dancing in hall 8 on the ocassion of diwali, sab log bas group m circle bnakar tujhe hi taad rahe the. I always figured a part of me in you, I never missed a chance to brag about you infront of people. Dhyaan se dekhiye iss masoom se chehre k peeche chipe stud launde ko, jispar ladkiyaan marti hai, but bhai sahab bhaav nahi dete, Bhai Badminton m jo maarta tha tu hmesha yaad rahega. text: Yo manish bhai! From the day one this memoir thing got famous, you're one of the topmost personality in my mind about whom I wanna bragg a lot. poore 4 saal m tumse bas complex hi khaya m, itna bada auhda hai tumhara, as far as I know all the people in IITK respect you except shrey:), and I got added to that list as well after long walk adventures we did together in the lit moonlight breaking the silence of untravelled roads of IIT including RM and the best thing I could remember in those golden moments were your choice of songs, bhai meri playlist change kara di tumne. I felt guilt on myself that I wasn't able to meet you in my early part of engineering, wish I could have known you earlier, your influence might have changed my life to a greater extent. I felt proud whenever I got a chance to sit beside you. I leaned countless things just by observing your character and most important one is that you taught me "poeple matter a lot in your life". Canteen wale bhaiya se lekar, IITK ki kitni bhi badi hasti tumahra naam zaroor jaanti hai. Kaas m iss zinda dil insaan se thoda phle mila hota. Pichhle 1.5 saal m jo backchodi miss ki usko 1 mahine m poora karne m bahut bhoomika nibhayi tumne. Shaam ko canteen m chai se jo backchodi suru hoti, wo OAT, CC, NCL, hote hue, IME building m break lena, RM k top floor par chain ki saans lena, Park 67 m ghusne ki naakam kosis karna, fir director bunglow k saamne ek legendary race ka countdown tumne hi kiya tha. Tumahre saath illegal tareeke se campus k bahar dekhi gayi holi, aur fir wo GH k saamne kheli hui holi, I'm gonnna remember that in my finest moments of my college life. Jaate jaate alvida khne ka moka to nahi mila, par zindgi m wapas milne ki khwahis zaroor rahegi mere andar.... miss you brother...keep in touch :)

text:
Yo! First of all, thank you for helping me out in MTH, the surge in my mth grades is highly correlated with you helping me out with the tough ones (ji haan, hum jaise nadan balako ke liye tough the wo..abhi tak geometry nahi pata kya hai mujhe XD). Spending time in RM and astro club with you and Gulati had a lasting, serene quality to it because it just felt inexplicably right. No social pressures, annoying obligations, or a need to constantly filter what I'm saying..I was in my natural habitat when you both were around. Maybe that's why we had so much fun in simple things like cycling around the campus, screening movies in astro club, lounging in RM, sharing meals in Chick Blast (or in Sandy's room lol) or the not so simple (and extremely fun) 'trip' to IIT Bombay for inter IIT XD. BTW I didn't know you were a snack monster! RM third floor Bakarwadi, chowpati snacks on the beaches of Bombay, endless deliveries from zomato itna jata kaha hai? Maybe that super brain of yours requires constant fuel. US-Canada boundary kood ke visit karna, we'll always have a Disneyland ticket for you.

P.S. - We've watched one of the most entertaining football matches together, dogs pasand nahi koi baat nahi but ab football follow karna padega.
author: Kushagra  Gupta

text:
Technically, you are one of my oldest friend in IITK XD, and congratulations yet again for escaping the joyride called MTH. Despite that, most of our memories are far and scattered. No worries, we are sure to make up for the lost time at Stanford.  One of the easiest and most fun people to talk to, I forget about time when I'm chatting with you, with only my mother's  5 a.m. alarm making me realise that we've been talking for hours. Our conversations spanning suicidal cats, the (super) tramp lifestyle, filthy rich aerodynamic hobbies, elder sister kidnapper tendencies, weird eagerness to sell our houses (while our families live in them) are some of the craziest and most interesting I've ever had. But I've also come to know a different side of you over our conversations with Leluna and incidents of the recent past. And that makes me all the more excited about our friendship in the future! I couldn't have asked for a better flatmate to share my journey at Stanford. 

P.P.S. - Dis civet cat. Kood gaya. R.I.P.

Bahut ho gayi serious baat, tune hamare pariwaar ka naam roshan kiya baapu ko bahu dilaayi aur wo bhi hame maar khilaaye bina unlike Jaspreet.

P.S.-Keep smiling aur Neha ka saath mat chhodna , mujhe prem kahaniyaan anjaam tak pahunte dekhne mein achha mahsoos hota hai.

Tumahar bhrata

text: The Ultimate God of IITK!! Bhai, you are literally one of the most intelligent people I've known. I was so fortunate to have you as a partner in all my courses and assignments. Main legit C/D khaata saare courses mein agar tu nahi hota to. Tere baare mein kaafi suna tha class 10th se hi, and fiitjee mein kaafi hype bana rakhi thi logon ne tere baare mein. Main darta tha shuru mein tere se baat karne se kyunki teri alag hi level thi. Par college mein aake first interaction hua tere saath and laga ye to kaafi chill banda hai üòÖ. Apni aadhi jharkhand group tere hi wing mein thi isliye kaafi achchi dosti ho gayi sabse. Kaafi gaaliyan sunni padi hai tere se over the time for my weak GK and poor logical reasoning üòî, hope karta hun improve ho jaye dheere dheere. Mujhe abhi bhi yaad hai tune bed tod diya tha ek din but shivam and tumne milkar le li thi meri free ki üò•. And uske baad umang ke saath meri GK quiz üòì, pata nhi us video ka kya hua, hopefully hamesha ke liye delete ho gaya ho üòå. Kaafi saare assignments and bakaiti ki hai tere saath and kaafi maza aaya, subhajit sir ki chapter to top pe rahegi üòõ. Codefundo, ICPC, Organization, OS, FinEco, ML sab cheez bhai-bhai ki tarah kiya hai humlogon ne. Bas ek hi cheez adhoori reh gayi, final sem ki chai and chill in the garden üòî, but hopefully gurgaon mein iski bhi time mil jayegi kabhi üòÖ. Baaki teri future ka to pata nahi, kaafi variable plan rehti hai teri (IAS, PhD, Quant, .... what's next? Management?) but jo bhi karega usme chaapega hi tu. All the best and hopefully jald hi milte hain!! ‚ù§Ô∏è
author: Ayush  Kumar

text: Hey bro, It's been a long time since I've known you and one thing I can say for sure is that we started off as brothers and we will go off as brothers. You were always the guy I used to get positive motivation from. Very active, sporty, always optimistic, always on time and always planning ahead is how I would describe you. You were always so punctual, that I used used to rely on you more than my alarm (remember all my wake-up texts on the night before each exam). From our random bulla sessions to our OS assignment hangouts to my last day photoshoot, all moments go into my memory-bag. I still remember the night when your laptop erased a full-day worth of OS code you had written and you still had the determination to write all of that again. We planned to hit the gym together so many times, but it never happened :(. I still hope that you go to the gym with me someday in the future or maybe at least teach me your basketball tactics :P. I wish you all the best for all your future endeavours, and no doubt you will succeed in whichever avenue you proceed. Hope to meet you soon!!
author: Ayush  Kumar

text:
Math God, Active Procrastinator, Pizza Lover, ChocoPie Distributor and what not!! You were my closest friend at IITK and my goto person for doubts, questions, random bulla, scientific/unscientific talk, help, enlightenment, imaginative theories, jokes, depression talk, w**d, or literally anything that a human could think of. There are so many memories we have together that it is hard to recall all of them. You started off as a quiet smart guy, but soon became our teacher in every course. I vividly remember the long tiring talk you gave on Goodstein's Theorem in the first year which none of us quite understood but it was still so fun listening to it. The canteen and pizza hangouts were my favourite. Pepper Barbecue Medium (plus an extra slice from my pizza), Maggi and Cheese Frankie was the the only thing you ever ate üòõ. Your room was like an open theatre of knowledge. One could come in at any time of the night, and be certain to leave with a substantial amount of mathematical/philosophical knowledge üòõ. 

You helping me to my feet when I was down was the norm, whether it was the Antaragni night when I was too hungover to walk, or the galaxy finals when I twisted my ankle hobbling down the stairs in excitement. It was hurtful to see your love for S***** P remain unconfessed üò•. It goes without saying that you are one of the smartest people I've met, and the most intense and profound math lover, the most surprising thing is how you achieve this with your god level last-minute decision-making skills (maybe procrastination is the solution to all our problems). Nothing can replace the awesome 4 years (minus 1 üòì) I had with you. Wish you all the best in all your endeavors in the US (and in finding true love üòõ), hope to see you soon!! ‚ù§Ô∏è
author: Ayush  Kumar

text: Munmun, Haga, Harshaga, no matter what we call you, you'll always be the bubbly, cheerful, smiling guy I know. From dancing to searching research internships (remember going to senior dorms late night fishing for advice üòÖ), preparing for interviews (which I screwed up sadly üò™), collaborating in assignments and quizzes, NLP project, CS610 (we set a new benchmark for collaboration and bitching together üòõ) and the Goa Trip, we have been together through all these times. We first met in the dancing group where I quickly became the notorious fraudy, and you were the only one who gave me hope that maybe I wasn't the worst dancer (sorry lol üòõ). You were my goto person for personal advice, CS talk, random gossip, asking treats (none of which you ever gave üòî) and for help. Being an introvert, you were the much needed friend to pull me out of my bubble and help me meet other smart people (including you). How would I have ever learnt how to fake smile and click good photos if you weren't there as my mentor üòõ. You are the most honest and open friend I've had. I can literally talk to you about anything without thinking twice, because I know we are bros. Thank you for making my IITK life a hundred times happier, worthful and easier üòå. God knows what hole of depression I'd have been in had I not found you. I hope no matter how far away you are, do not forget what this emoji means üë¨, "Bhai hai tu mera..". Also, good luck in finding Korean women and do bring back Samsung Watches for me. Hope to see you soon!! ‚ù§Ô∏è
author: Ayush  Kumar

text: Hey there roomie and bro, frankly I can say that no one has heard more of your weird-ass alarm-tone than me üòõ. author: Baldip Singh Bijlani

text:
Bhai tere mail id mein 2004 kyu aata hai.  Anyways, Sanghi bhai. Tere chakkar mein bahut sidiya chadi hai bhaiüòÖ. But worth it for your company. Tu literally mera academic mentor raha hai. Mein chein ki nind sota tha yeh sochke ki assignment to sanghi kara hi dega. 

But sabh se zyada important tune mera perspective badla tha padhai ke baare mein. You had a huge hand in making be process oriented rather than goal oriented making my journey much more enjoyable. (Feel free to construct double meaning about the previous sentenceü§£). 

Pehli job gurgaon mein lagi hai. Ghar zarur aana. See you soon bhai.
author: Baldip Singh Bijlani

text:
Before starting to write memoirs, I made a list of people by how I knew them, clubs, department, social circles, etc. You were on every single one of those lists. 

You have done the fastest 180 I've ever seen. The first time I worked with you on any assignment, we were taking a break in the dosa canteen. You said and I quote "bhai abhi itna kucch padhna hai, pata hai Fermat's last theorem ka proof 129 pages ka hai, abh nhi padhenge to kabh" üòÖ. Exactly one year after that, "bhai os ka assignment karwaane aajao", and then leaving saying "abe jitne ho ske krdena, mein khane ja rha" and coming back after I submitted it. 

I've always loved your impeccable sense of hunour, timing and an extremely course social filter. I remember you saying to Mainak sir during CS220 endsem paper distribution, while he was writing the course averages, highest, etc. in the most confident voice ever, "Sir I urge you to write in hexadecimal", üòÇproviding much needed comical reprieve to everyone.

 I have enjoyed witty wordplay and weirdly inappropriate yet funny mom jokes many times, even though I have been on the receiving end more often than I would have liked. üòÖ

I have had a lot of fun, working with you on every group assignment we have done(even if you did not worküòã). I enjoyed our after assignment submission parties in UC/Dominos/Hall 1 canteen/Chickblast even more. Loved debating with you on the same team, whenever I got the opportunity to do so. 

You have been with me when I did all stupid stuff for the first time, alcohol, w***, taking VR prematurelyüòÖ. 

I am sure that you have given much more back to people at IITK, than you have received. Love you brother. Keep in touch. No excuses, you will be in Gurgaon as well.
author: Baldip Singh Bijlani

text: Bhai orientation mein kaafi view block kiya tuneüòÜ. (Context : Ayush is 201,im 203, and he is way taller). Pe mein bhi bahut maze aaye tere saath. Sadly usske baad zyada baat nhi huiüòï. But parallel ka chutiyap kabhi nhi bolunga üòÖ. See you soon buddy!
author: Baldip Singh Bijlani

text:
Sorry bhai tera memoir likhne mein itni der kardi. I've realised ki tere saath itni memories ki select karna impossible hai. 

Apni banni pehli baar 2nd year mein start hui thi, aur kabhi band nhi huiüòÖ. Tere saath kabhi bhi kaam kro toh maza bahut aata hai kyunki tu hamesha khush aur positive rehta hai. OS ki deadline se pehle aag waali patang udane jaata hai. Parallel ke assignment krte same, Reliance colony aur kota ke kissey sunata hai. Pata hai nhi hoga kuchh, toh bhi bolega tension mat le ho jayegaüòÉ. 

Tu had se zyada humble aur self aware hai. Aman ko bolo teri height kam hai to jawab milega, "üò°Almost same to hai", Tujhe bolo ki bowling thodi dhire hai, jawab milega "üòïHaan yaar spin zyada tez hai". But trust me, you are very smart and talented, never sell yourself short. 

Aage se mein bolunga Sanghi, Singhal pehle Param ko lenge, woh nhi maana, toh kisi AUR mast bande ko le lenge. (Samajhne waale samajh gye) üòâ. 

Love you brother. Milte rehna, aur apni show recommendations jaari rkhna.
author: Baldip Singh Bijlani

text:
Asati bhai. Tujhse acchi advice kahi nhi mili. Bahut mature aadmi hai tu. Ta 202 mein support ke liye thanks. Tere saath jivan ka aur jain samaj ka kaafi gyan mila hai
Nha liya kar bas

Thanks for all your help in courses. Let's watch a match at Lord's soon. Even an ODI is fine is a test is too long for your busy assüòÖ. 
Best of luck.

text:
Yaar tera and srajit ka memoir kaafi same ho jayga‚Ä¶hona hi h :D!!!

Yaar tum logo se gaali khaane me alag hi maza aata tha! Gaali de de ke Introvert Deb ko thoda bakchodi karna sikhaya, iske liye to bohot saara thanks.
Bakchodi waali baate to thik h, but har sem tere saath koi na koi course kiya hi h na! mth, fir esc, phir mso, fir DS‚Ä¶yaar inke memories bhi kitne mast h. Saale har week aake tu merese zabardasti esc201 assignment karwata tha, bohot gussa aata tha tab XD. And intern prep bhi kitna mast time tha(wo alag baat ki aap saanp banke hum bhaiyo ko chhodke day1 laga liye‚Ä¶.dost ki intern na lage to dukh hota hai, but dost day1 laga le to aur dukh hota h :(.   )
IITK me apna last scene to yaar‚Ä¶.kya hi batau, mujhe kabhi laga nhi tha ki waisa hoga.
Memories to bohot huye‚Ä¶ek line tumhare liye bhi likhte h‚Ä¶.
Tere jaisa confident, decisive, both chill and serious, thoda mc but overall bohot acha insaan aur nhi hoga. Love you man!
Aur saale parental supervision(matlab mera and Srajit ka) k alawa peena mat‚Ä¶.bank account khali ho jayga XD.
author: Debmalya  Sarkar

Tere chakkar me dance tak seekh liya bhai, 1st year ka Deb to ye soch bhi nhi sakhta tha XD!!!
